text.section:
In determining whether a policy or contract is readable within the meaning of this section the commissioner shall consider, at least, the following factors:
The simplicity of the sentence structure and the shortness of the sentences used;
The extent to which commonly used and understood words are employed;
The extent to which legal terms are avoided;
The extent to which references to other sections or provisions of the contract are minimized;
The extent to which definitional provisions are incorporated in the text of the policy or contract; and
Any additional factors relevant to the readability or understandability of an insurance policy or contract which the commissioner may prescribe by regulation.
